OL,3,CParents sue hospital that 'missed
OL,4,Copportunities' before death of little
OL,5,Cgirl
OL,7,FTest revealed Ryleigh had
OL,8,F"extraordinarily high" levels of
OL,9,FCreatine Kinase (CK) in her blood,
OL,10,Faround 2,000 the normal amount which
OL,11,Fis life-threatening.
OL,13,FDespite medical colleagues from Leeds
OL,14,Fadvising further investigation into
OL,15,Fher symptoms, this was not followed up
OL,16,Fby hospital staff in Blackpool, the
OL,17,Finquest heard.
OL,19,FDoctors allowed Ryleigh to go home
OL,20,Fwith her parents, with a follow-up
OL,21,Fplanned for six to eight weeks.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/10
